### Description

I have noticed a strange behavior when using the select functionality. It does not seem to work to select the first element of a select input using the `$browser->select('name', 'value')` method. Every other `option` can be selected but not the first one. 

This is maybe related to #1075

I'm using Inertia with React and shadcn components. 

### Steps To Reproduce

1. Create a simple Page with an select component

```php
class MyController {
  public function show() {
    return Inertia::render('show');
  }
}
```

```tsx
export default function Show() {
  return (
    <Select name="mySelect" data-dusk="mySelect">
      <SelectTrigger>
        <SelectValue placeholder="Select an item"/>
      </SelectTrigger>
      <SelectContent>
        <SelectItem value="first">First Value</SelectItem>
        <SelectItem value="second">First Value</SelectItem>
      </SelectContent>
    </Select>
  );
}
```

2. Create the dusk test case

```php
// Here the value is not selected
it('dose not select correct value', function () {
  $this->browse(function(Browser $browser){
    $browser->visit('/show')
      ->waitFor('@mySelect')
      ->select('mySelect', 'first')
      ->screenshot('wrong');
  });
});

// Here everything works fine
it('dose not select correct value', function () {
  $this->browse(function(Browser $browser){
    $browser->visit('/show')
      ->waitFor('@mySelect')
      ->select('mySelect', 'second')
      ->screenshot('correct');
  });
});
```

If the order of the `SelectItem` elements is changed  in the react component, the select for the value `first` works but not for `second`.

